CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh courier newspaper, December 9, 1972, pg. 9 reads: "Out-Of-Towners At Affair - Joining Pittsburghers at the Urban League Guild's Dinner Dance were a number of out-of-towners. Included were the above group who are from left to right: Art Greene and Arthur Gittens (guests of Irma Johnson) of New York: Mr. and Mrs. William Jones, Jr. (Guests of Ruby Bowe) of Detroit, Mich.; Mr. and Mrs. Sell Thomas, Washington, Pa.; Ed Honorat of Haiti (guest of Barbara McCants); Mr. and Mrs. Carl Williams, (guests of Mr. and Mrs. W.C.Rainey) of Cleveland, and Mrs. D.H. Allen (guest of Ruth Vannall) of Huntington, W.Va."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Art Greene, Arthur Gittens, Mr. and Mrs. William Jones, Jr., Mr. and Mrs. Sell Thomas, Ed Honorat, Mr. and Mrs. Carl Williams, and Mrs. D.H. Allen, posed in Allegheny Club for the Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh dinner dance, Three Rivers Stadium
